<!-- WHY THIS AREA -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Prestige family suburb with heritage-listed Queenslanders and low stock.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Clayfield is one of Brisbane's most consistently sought-after inner north-east suburbs. Its tree-lined streets, heritage-listed Queenslanders and position within the inner north's private school corridor have kept it as a target suburb for established families and discerning buyers for decades. It sits alongside Ascot and Hamilton as part of the prestige northside market, but with a different character: quieter, more residential, and with a housing stock that is genuinely difficult to replicate in newer suburbs.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
<div style="background:#fff; border-left:4px solid #c4912a; padding:2rem 2rem 1.75rem; margin:2rem 0;">
  <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.72rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.18em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Free Appraisal</p>
  <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.4rem; font-weight:300; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.25rem; line-height:1.25;">Find out what your Clayfield home is worth.</h3>
  <form method="POST" action="https://formspree.io/f/xnjgedwp" style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.75rem;">
  <input type="text" name="_gotcha" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" style="display:none" />
    <input type="hidden" name="_next" value="https://danielgierach.com/thank-you?from=suburb-appraisal" />
    <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="Appraisal enquiry: Clayfield" />
    <input type="hidden" name="_source" value="clayfield" />
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:0.75rem;" class="suburb-form-grid">
      <input type="text" name="name" required placeholder="Your name" autocomplete="name"
        style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.88rem; padding:0.7rem 0.9rem; border:1px solid rgba(28,25,23,0.18); background:#faf9f7; color:#1c1917; outline:none; width:100%; box-sizing:border-box;" />
      <input type="email" name="email" required placeholder="Email address" autocomplete="email"
        style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.88rem; padding:0.7rem 0.9rem; border:1px solid rgba(28,25,23,0.18); background:#faf9f7; color:#1c1917; outline:none; width:100%; box-sizing:border-box;" />
    </div>
    <input type="text" name="property_address" required placeholder="Your Clayfield address (street + number)"
      style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.88rem; padding:0.7rem 0.9rem; border:1px solid rgba(28,25,23,0.18); background:#faf9f7; color:#1c1917; outline:none; width:100%; box-sizing:border-box;" />
    <div style="display:flex; gap:0.75rem; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <button type="submit"
        style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.78rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; background:#c4912a; color:#1c1917; padding:0.75rem 1.75rem; border:none; cursor:pointer; white-space:nowrap;">
        Request my free appraisal
      </button>
      <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:300; color:#78716c; margin:0; line-height:1.5;">Daniel will be in touch promptly. No pressure.</p>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>
<style>
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .suburb-form-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
  }
</style>
<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The buyer profile in Clayfield is concentrated at the top end of the family market: long-term owner-occupiers who purchased in the suburb for its school catchment and character, established professionals who have been watching the suburb for years before committing, and occasionally interstate buyers who understand the northside prestige corridor and are purchasing with genuine knowledge of where Clayfield sits within it. Stock turnover is low, which means well-presented homes attract serious buyers rather than casual lookers.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Clayfield Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner North-East Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Prestige Heritage Market</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Heritage Queenslanders, low turnover</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/wooloowin" style="color:#c4912a;">Wooloowin</a>, <a href="/suburbs/nundah" style="color:#c4912a;">Nundah</a>, <a href="/suburbs/ascot" style="color:#c4912a;">Ascot</a>, <a href="/suburbs/hamilton" style="color:#c4912a;">Hamilton</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Clayfield.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the median house price in Clayfield Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Clayfield sits at the prestige end of the inner north-east market. Heritage-listed Queenslanders and large character homes on generous blocks trade in a range that reflects the suburb's position alongside Ascot and Hamilton. Stock is limited and demand from quality buyers is consistent. Contact Daniel for a current appraisal on your specific property.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Clayfield?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Clayfield's stock is genuinely low-turnover. When a quality home is presented well and priced on recent evidence, it attracts serious buyers quickly. Heritage Queenslanders tend to sell within 25 to 45 days when the campaign is well-targeted. The prestige end of the market can run longer depending on the depth of the buyer pool at a given price level.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Clayfield Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Clayfield is one of Brisbane's most private and settled inner suburbs. The tree-lined streets, the character of the original housing stock, and the proximity to the Ascot and Hamilton dining precincts give it a sense of established permanence. Clayfield College and access to the inner north's private school corridor are significant drawcards for families making long-term location decisions.</p>
      </details>
      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What types of homes are in Clayfield?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Clayfield is dominated by heritage Queenslanders, interwar homes and character properties on medium to large blocks. Heritage listings constrain alterations for many of the suburb's most recognisable homes, which preserves the streetscape but requires sellers to understand the implications for presentation. There is a smaller apartment and townhouse layer near the Sandgate Road and Lutwyche Road boundaries.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

